                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Cox, an omnibus conductor—on the afternoon of the 1st of April I was in Gracechurch Street carry<lb></lb>ing a bag—I had a purse in my jacket containing 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5 3/4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and a dupli<lb></lb>cate—the prisoner came and put his hand in my pocket, took my purse, and ran across the road—I told a gentleman, who ran after him—the prisoner ran into a constable's arms—I charged him.</p>
